library(tidyverse)
library(reactable)
library(reactablefmtr)
library(htmltools)

set.seed(45)
# import and clean data
df <- rio::import(here::here("data", "df_theory.xlsx")) %>%
    janitor::clean_names() %>%
    fill(year:paradigm, .direction = "down")

htmltools::tags$a(href = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mkezer/ea-database/main/df.xlsx",
    download = "df_theory.xlsx", "Download Data", style = "display: inline-block; padding: 6px 12px; background-color: #007BFF; color: white; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 10px;")
Download Data 
title <- "Empirical Studies on Empathic Accuracy: Ickes & Dial Paradigms"
subtitle1 <- "Click on the triangle on the left for the abstract"
subtitle2 <- "Scroll right to see the finding"

reactable(df, searchable = TRUE, striped = TRUE, highlight = TRUE, bordered = TRUE,
    defaultPageSize = 5, wrap = TRUE, filterable = TRUE, details = function(index) {
        htmltools::div(htmltools::strong("Abstract: "), df$abstract[index], htmltools::br(),
            htmltools::strong("Findings: "), df$findings[index])
    }, columns = list(year = colDef(name = "Year", filterable = TRUE, align = "center",
        width = 80), author = colDef(name = "Author(s)", filterable = TRUE), title = colDef(name = "Title",
        filterable = TRUE), journal = colDef(name = "Journal", filterable = TRUE),
        rqs = colDef(name = "Research Questions", minWidth = 250, maxWidth = 400,
            align = "left"), hs = colDef(name = "Hypotheses", minWidth = 250, maxWidth = 400,
            align = "left"), findings = colDef(name = "Findings", minWidth = 300,
            maxWidth = 500, align = "left"), abstract = colDef(name = "Abstract",
            show = FALSE))) %>%
    add_title(title) %>%
    add_subtitle(subtitle1, font_size = 16) %>%
    add_subtitle(subtitle2, font_size = 16)
